  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat your oven to 180°C."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get a pot of salted water to a boil."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop your courgette and peppers into small chunks. Place them on a baking tray, drizzle over some olive oil, season with salt and pepper, and pop them into the oven for 20 mins, until starting to char and crisp up."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, wash your spinach and pat dry with a paper towel."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop your white cabbage, cucumber and avocado into small chunks. Finely slice your spring onions. Add these all to a large salad bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place your tomatoes on the baking tray with your courgettes and peppers and drizzle them with a bit of oil before popping the tray back in the oven for 5 mins, until done to your liking."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Put your pasta in the boiling water, drain using a colander once al dente."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Fry your bacon until crispy."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make the mayo, start by roughly chopping your garlic, shallot, avocado and herbs. Add these all to a blender or food processor, along with the juice of half a lemon, water, and spinach. Add your mayonnaise and give it a blitz."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roughly chop your bacon into bite-sized pieces before adding it to your salad bowl along with your roasted vegetables and avo mayo dressing. Give it a good toss and finish with some lemon zest. Enjoy."
    }
  ],
